page.title: 09ECOLOGY IN LOWICK.
page.content: In a 14 metre stretch of hedgerow leading to the church were found: Hawthorn, Elder, Sycamore, Dogrose, Bramble, Ash, White Bryony, Ivy, Lady's Bedstraw, Cleavers, Dandylion, White Campion, Nettles, Speedwell, Chickweed, Cow Parsley, Bugle, Thistle, Cocksfoot, Timothy, Sweet Vernall Grass, Cranesbill, Jack-by-the-hedge, Daisy, Plantain, Moss, Mayweed and Common Sorrel. Creatures spotted were: Orange-tip and Small Heath butterflies, Hawthorn Moth caterpillers, Froghoppers Ladybirds, Honeybees, Spiders and violet ground beetles.
